@3<>
Hello  my name is Terry Green.  I  have
had  an  Amiga A1200 for over 5  years,
one day I thought that I would start  a
Public  Domain Software  Library,   and
not  being able to afford  to  pay  for
advertising  I  put an  advert  in  our
local  Admag,  a free ads paper,   ever
since  then  I have had people  phoning
me  and asking for advice on how to  do
things on the Amiga computer.  So  with
me knowing a little bit about a lot  of
things  I  thought I know I will  start
an  Amiga HelpLine to give free  advice
about all things Amigan.
@4
The  only trouble was I don't  know  an
awful lot,  so I put an advert  in  the
Admag and Amiga Format Readers Ads.  My
helpLine  has  now  grown  to  over  40
people  who  are willing  and  able  to




give  advice  on  most  things  of  the
Amigan.
If  anyone feels that they  can  be  of
help  to  anybody else  and  that  they
want  to  join  my Amiga HelpLine  they
can contact me at.#8 01709-814-296@4
Write to me at@7
Terry Green (TGPD Software)
8 Clarence Place
Maltby
Rotherham
South Yorkshire
